
compressed files are split into 2 types, single file compressed and
archive.  single files get analyzed to identify the primary file content
and re-classified.  archives are identified and re-classified as containers.

excessively large archives (E.L.A.) will be indexed and maintained as-is.
moderate archives will be extracted and maintained as a folder-container
    this will allow the system to choose an appropriate archival tool
    based on performance and overall preferences.

the expectation for E.L.A.s is that the contents will be extracted into
more unit sized containers and once all data is processed the E.L.A. will
be purged.

identifying E.L.A.s will be based on actual size and some other properties
like complexity of structure of the contents.
